  .panel
    .panel-body
      %h3.m-t-xxs= t('privacy.title')
      
      %p This is the web site of Jinglr. Our postal address is: 
      %address{:style => "margin: 0 0 20px 0; display: block;"}
        %span{:style => "display: block;"} Orpheux Design
        %span{:style => "display: block;"} c/o Jinglr
        %span{:style => "display: block;"} 90 SW 3RD ST, #3101
        %span{:style => "display: block;"} Miami, FL 33130
      
      %p We can be reached via email at #{mail_to("info@jinglr.com", "info@jinglr.com", :encode => "javascript")}. For each visitor to our Web page, our Web server automatically recognizes the user's domain name and email address (where possible).
      
      %h3 What we collect.
      
      %p We collect the domain name and email address (where possible) of visitors to our Web page, aggregate information on what pages users access or visit, information volunteered by the user, such as survey information and/or site registrations. The information we collect is used to improve the content of our Web page, used to customize the content and/or layout of our page for each individual visitor and.
      
      %p With respect to cookies: We use cookies to record session information, such as audio files that users are listening to, or currently active users, to customize Web page content based on visitors' browser type or other information that the visitor sends.
      
      %p If you do not want to receive email from us in the future, please let us know by sending us email at the above address.
      
      %h3 What we do with your info.
      
      %p We do not share personally identifiable information such as name, email, phone number, or address with any organizations unless required by federal law.
      
      %p If you supply us with your location online you are granting us permission to display portions of it to visitors of the web site.
      
      %p If you supply a Jinglr member with your postal address you are granting them permission to use it to contact you and/or send correspondence.
      
      %p With respect to Ad Servers: To try and bring you offers that are of interest to you, we have relationships with other companies that we allow to place ads on our Web pages. As a result of your visit to our site, ad server companies may collect information such as your domain type, your IP address and clickstream information. For further information, consult the privacy policies of: #{link_to("http://www.google.com/privacy.html")}
      
      %p From time to time, we may use customer information for new, unanticipated uses not previously disclosed in our privacy notice. If our information practices change at some time in the future we will post the policy changes to our Web site to notify you of these changes and we will use for these new purposes only data collected from the time of the policy change forward. If you are concerned about how your information is used, you should check back at our Web site periodically.
      
      %h3 What you can do about your info.
      
      %p Users may prevent their information from being used for purposes other than those for which it was originally collected by emailing us at the above address. Upon request we provide site visitors with access to a description of information that we maintain about them.
      
      %p Users can access this information by email us at the above address. Upon request we offer visitors no ability to have factual inaccuracies corrected in information that we maintain about them
      
      %p If you feel that this site is not following its stated information policy, you may contact us at the above addresses or phone number, The DMA's Committee on Ethical Business Practices at mgoldberger@the-dma.org, state or local chapters of the Better Business Bureau, state or local user protection office, The Federal Trade Commission by phone at 202.FTC-HELP (202.382.4357) or electronically at http://www.ftc.gov/ftc/complaint.htm.
      
